[log] bash[68] stdout #### Hardware Control Mode
[log] bash[68] stdout **The `RCControl` class provides hardware control interface**
[log] bash[68] stdout ```python
[log] bash[68] stdout class RCControl(object):
[log] bash[68] stdout     def __init__(self, serial_port):
[log] bash[68] stdout         # Initialize serial port
[log] bash[68] stdout         self.serial_port = serial_port
[log] bash[68] stdout         self.ser = serial.Serial(self.serial_port, 115200, timeout=1)
[log] bash[68] stdout     def steer(self, prediction):
[log] bash[68] stdout         if prediction == 2:
[log] bash[68] stdout             self.ser.write(b'1')
[log] bash[68] stdout             print("Forward")
[log] bash[68] stdout         elif prediction == 0:
[log] bash[68] stdout             self.ser.write(b'2')
[log] bash[68] stdout             print("Left")
[log] bash[68] stdout         elif prediction == 1:
[log] bash[68] stdout             self.ser.write(b'3')
[log] bash[68] stdout             print("Right")
[log] bash[68] stdout     def stop(self):
[log] bash[68] stdout         self.ser.write(b'4')
[log] bash[68] stdout ```
[log] bash[68] stdout Usage: `rc_car = RCControl("/dev/tty.usbmodem1421")` then call `rc_car.steer(prediction)` or `rc_car.stop()`
