[log] bash[68] stdout ### Node 2: Real - time Video Stream Processing
[log] bash[68] stdout **Function Description**: Process the real - time video stream from the Raspberry Pi camera, realizing JPEG format decoding, image pre - processing, ROI extraction, and frame buffer management. It supports low - latency video data transmission and processing.
[log] bash[68] stdout **Core Algorithms**:
[log] bash[68] stdout - JPEG stream parsing and frame extraction
[log] bash[68] stdout - Image format conversion and pre - processing
[log] bash[68] stdout - ROI (Region of Interest) extraction
[log] bash[68] stdout - Frame buffer management
[log] bash[68] stdout - Real - time display processing
[log] bash[68] stdout ```python
[log] bash[68] stdout stream_bytes = b' '
[log] bash[68] stdout while True:
[log] bash[68] stdout     stream_bytes += self.rfile.read(1024)
[log] bash[68] stdout     first = stream_bytes.find(b'\xff\xd8')
[log] bash[68] stdout     last = stream_bytes.find(b'\xff\xd9')
[log] bash[68] stdout     if first != -1 and last != -1:
[log] bash[68] stdout         jpg = stream_bytes[first:last + 2]
[log] bash[68] stdout         stream_bytes = stream_bytes[last + 2:]
[log] bash[68] stdout         gray = cv2.imdecode(np.frombuffer(jpg, dtype=np.uint8), cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
[log] bash[68] stdout         image = cv2.imdecode(np.frombuffer(jpg, dtype=np.uint8), cv2.IMREAD_COLOR)
[log] bash[68] stdout         # lower half of the image
[log] bash[68] stdout         height, width = gray.shape
[log] bash[68] stdout         roi = gray[int(height/2):height, :]
[log] bash[68] stdout         
[log] bash[68] stdout         cv2.imshow('image', image)
[log] bash[68] stdout         
[log] bash[68] stdout         # reshape image
[log] bash[68] stdout         image_array = roi.reshape(1, int(height/2) * width).astype(np.float32)
[log] bash[68] stdout ```
