[log] bash[68] stdout ### Node 5: Distance Measurement
[log] bash[68] stdout **Function Description**: Measure the position information of the target object in the image and calculate distance based on camera parameters. Uses camera intrinsic matrix and triangulation principle to compute distance from detected objects.
[log] bash[68] stdout **Core Algorithms**:
[log] bash[68] stdout - Camera geometric model
[log] bash[68] stdout - Triangulation principle
[log] bash[68] stdout - Distance calculation formula
[log] bash[68] stdout - Camera intrinsic matrix parameters
[log] bash[68] stdout ```python
[log] bash[68] stdout class DistanceToCamera(object):
[log] bash[68] stdout     def __init__(self):
[log] bash[68] stdout         # camera params
[log] bash[68] stdout         self.alpha = 8.0 * math.pi / 180    # degree measured manually
[log] bash[68] stdout         self.v0 = 119.865631204             # from camera matrix
[log] bash[68] stdout         self.ay = 332.262498472             # from camera matrix
[log] bash[68] stdout     def calculate(self, v, h, x_shift, image):
[log] bash[68] stdout         # compute and return the distance from the target point to the camera
[log] bash[68] stdout         d = h / math.tan(self.alpha + math.atan((v - self.v0) / self.ay))
[log] bash[68] stdout         if d > 0:
[log] bash[68] stdout             cv2.putText(image, "%.1fcm" % d,
[log] bash[68] stdout                         (image.shape[1] - x_shift, image.shape[0] - 20),
[log] bash[68] stdout                         cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 0.7, (255, 255, 255), 2)
[log] bash[68] stdout         return d
[log] bash[68] stdout ```
