Plan created. Steps:
  - Set up the AutoRCCar project directory structure with all necessary __init__.py files including workspace, arduino, computer, computer/cascade_xml, computer/chess_board, and raspberryPi directories.
  - Create the environment.yml file with all required dependencies including opencv-python==4.12.0.88, numpy==2.2.6, scikit-learn==1.7.1, pygame==2.6.1, pyserial==3.5, and other specified packages.
  - Create pyproject.toml to make the project installable via pip with proper package metadata and dependencies.
  - Implement the load_data function in computer/model.py that loads training data from npz files and splits into training and validation sets.
  - Implement the NeuralNetwork class skeleton with __init__ method and create method in computer/model.py using OpenCV's ml module for MLP architecture.
  - Implement the train method in the NeuralNetwork class that performs back-propagation training using OpenCV's MLP trainer.
  - Implement the evaluate method in the NeuralNetwork class that computes model accuracy on test data.
  - Implement the predict method in the NeuralNetwork class that returns class labels for driving decisions.
  - Implement the save_model and load_model methods in the NeuralNetwork class for model persistence using OpenCV format.
  - Implement the RCControl class in computer/rc_driver_helper.py with __init__, steer, and stop methods for serial port car control.
  - Implement the DistanceToCamera class in computer/rc_driver_helper.py with __init__ and calculate methods using camera intrinsic parameters.
  - Implement the ObjectDetection class in computer/rc_driver_helper.py with __init__ and detect methods using cascade classifier for stop sign and traffic light detection.
  - Implement the Server class in computer/rc_driver.py that handles multi-threaded network server setup for video and sensor data ports.
  - Implement the SensorDataHandler class in computer/rc_driver.py for receiving ultrasonic sensor data via network socket.
  - Implement the VideoStreamHandler class in computer/rc_driver.py with the handle method for JPEG stream decoding, object detection, distance calculation, and autonomous driving decision logic.
  - Implement the main entry point in computer/rc_driver.py with __main__ block that initializes the Server and starts the autonomous driving system.
  - Implement the CollectTrainingData class in computer/collect_training_data.py with network socket setup, pygame keyboard input handling, and data collection logic.
  - Install the package in development mode and verify that all basic module imports work correctly.
  - Write comprehensive test cases covering NeuralNetwork operations, RCControl, DistanceToCamera calculations, ObjectDetection, and data loading functionality.
  - Run the full test suite and fix any failures until all tests pass successfully.

