[log] bash[80] stdout ### Detailed Description of Configuration Classes
[log] bash[80] stdout #### 1. Server Configuration Class
[log] bash[80] stdout **Function**: Configure the connection parameters and port settings of the network server
[log] bash[80] stdout ```python
[log] bash[80] stdout class Server(object):
[log] bash[80] stdout     def __init__(self, host, port1, port2):
[log] bash[80] stdout         self.host = host          # Server host address
[log] bash[80] stdout         self.port1 = port1        # Video stream port
[log] bash[80] stdout         self.port2 = port2        # Sensor data port
[log] bash[80] stdout ```
[log] bash[80] stdout **Parameter Description**:
[log] bash[80] stdout - `host` (str): The server host address, such as "192.168.1.100"
[log] bash[80] stdout - `port1` (int): The video stream server port, default is 8000
[log] bash[80] stdout - `port2` (int): The sensor data server port, default is 8002
[log] bash[80] stdout **Usage Example**:
[log] bash[80] stdout ```python
[log] bash[80] stdout # Create a server instance
[log] bash[80] stdout server = Server("192.168.1.100", 8000, 8002)
[log] bash[80] stdout server.start()
[log] bash[80] stdout ```
[log] bash[80] stdout #### 2. VideoStreamHandler Configuration Class
[log] bash[80] stdout **Function**: Configure the parameters and threshold settings of the video stream processor
[log] bash[80] stdout ```python
[log] bash[80] stdout class VideoStreamHandler(socketserver.StreamRequestHandler):
[log] bash[80] stdout     # Object height parameters (manually measured)
[log] bash[80] stdout     h1 = 5.5  # Stop sign height (cm)
[log] bash[80] stdout     h2 = 5.5  # Traffic light height (cm)
[log] bash[80] stdout     
[log] bash[80] stdout     # Distance threshold configuration
[log] bash[80] stdout     d_sensor_thresh = 30      # Ultrasonic sensor stop threshold (cm)
[log] bash[80] stdout     d_stop_light_thresh = 25  # Stop sign and traffic light stop threshold (cm)
[log] bash[80] stdout     
[log] bash[80] stdout     # Time control parameters
[log] bash[80] stdout     stop_start = 0            # Stop start time
[log] bash[80] stdout     stop_finish = 0           # Stop finish time
[log] bash[80] stdout     stop_time = 0             # Stop duration
[log] bash[80] stdout     drive_time_after_stop = 0 # Driving time after stop
[log] bash[80] stdout ```
[log] bash[80] stdout **Configuration Parameter Description**:
[log] bash[80] stdout - `h1`, `h2` (float): The actual height of the target objects, used for distance calculation
[log] bash[80] stdout - `d_sensor_thresh` (int): The stop distance when the ultrasonic sensor detects an obstacle
[log] bash[80] stdout - `d_stop_light_thresh` (int): The stop distance for stop signs and traffic lights
[log] bash[80] stdout - `stop_start`, `stop_finish` (int): Records of stop timestamps
[log] bash[80] stdout - `stop_time` (float): The calculated stop duration
[log] bash[80] stdout - `drive_time_after_stop` (float): The driving time after stopping
[log] bash[80] stdout #### 3. CollectTrainingData Configuration Class
[log] bash[80] stdout **Function**: Configure the network and serial port parameters of the training data collector
[log] bash[80] stdout ```python
[log] bash[80] stdout class CollectTrainingData(object):
[log] bash[80] stdout     def __init__(self, host, port, serial_port, input_size):
[log] bash[80] stdout         self.server_socket = socket.socket()
[log] bash[80] stdout         self.server_socket.bind((host, port))
[log] bash[80] stdout         self.server_socket.listen(0)
[log] bash[80] stdout         
[log] bash[80] stdout         # Serial port connection configuration
[log] bash[80] stdout         self.ser = serial.Serial(serial_port, 115200, timeout=1)
[log] bash[80] stdout         
[log] bash[80] stdout         # Input size configuration
[log] bash[80] stdout         self.input_size = input_size
[log] bash[80] stdout         
[log] bash[80] stdout         # Label matrix configuration
[log] bash[80] stdout         self.k = np.zeros((4, 4), 'float')
[log] bash[80] stdout         for i in range(4):
[log] bash[80] stdout             self.k[i, i] = 1
[log] bash[80] stdout ```
[log] bash[80] stdout **Parameter Description**:
[log] bash[80] stdout - `host` (str): The host address of the data collection server
[log] bash[80] stdout - `port` (int): The port of the data collection server
[log] bash[80] stdout - `serial_port` (str): The path to the Arduino serial port device
[log] bash[80] stdout - `input_size` (int): The size of the input image (number of pixels)
[log] bash[80] stdout - `k` (np.ndarray): A 4x4 label matrix for one - hot encoding
[log] bash[80] stdout #### 4. RCControl Configuration Class
[log] bash[80] stdout **Function**: Configure the serial communication parameters of the RC car controller
[log] bash[80] stdout ```python
[log] bash[80] stdout class RCControl(object):
