[log] bash[80] stdout #### 5. DistanceToCamera Configuration Class
[log] bash[80] stdout **Function**: Configure the camera parameters of the camera distance calculator
[log] bash[80] stdout ```python
[log] bash[80] stdout class DistanceToCamera(object):
[log] bash[80] stdout     def __init__(self):
[log] bash[80] stdout         # Camera parameters (obtained through manual measurement and calibration)
[log] bash[80] stdout         self.alpha = 8.0 * math.pi / 180    # Camera viewing angle (in radians)
[log] bash[80] stdout         self.v0 = 119.865631204             # Camera matrix parameter v0
